Given the following FastAPI router code, review it for issues and improve it:

```python
from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException
from pydantic import BaseModel

app = FastAPI()

class Item(BaseModel):
    name: str
    price: float

items = {}

@app.post("/items")
def create(item: Item):
    id = str(len(items) + 1)
    items[id] = item
    return item

@app.get("/items/{id}")
def get(id: str):
    return items[id]

@app.delete("/items/{id}")
def delete(id: str):
    del items[id]
```

Fix: (1) use APIRouter instead of app directly, (2) add response_model annotations, (3) add proper status codes (201, 204), (4) add 404 handling for missing items, (5) add authentication dependency, (6) use descriptive function names.
